main event: A fluorescent green object was observed over Lake O'Neill, Camp Pendleton, California on April 21, 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as large, pale green, and fluorescent with two trailing edges,It changed shape from roundish to a teardrop shape during the observation,The object was observed by multiple witnesses from the Military Police Company,The sighting lasted from approximately 0420 to around 0510 hours, leading to the object's disappearance with incoming daylight,No photographs were taken of the sighting.
witness description: members of the Military Police Company
